{{!
  PROFILE CUSTOM CONTENT SNIPPET

  Adds the Inklings tab content to the character profile page.

  FILE: ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom.hbs

  IMPORTANT: This file might be empty or minimal if you don't have other custom profile content.

  STEP 1: Check the file contents
  1. Open your game's ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom.hbs
  2. Look at what's in the file:
     - If it's EMPTY or has only comments, use "OPTION A" below
     - If it has existing <div class="tab-content"> with other <div class="tab-pane">, use "OPTION B" below

  Copy ONLY this content:

  ---START COPY HERE---
  <div class="tab-pane fade" id="inklings-tab-pane">
    {{inklings-tab characterId=this.char.id characterName=this.char.name viewerId=this.viewer.id isStaff=this.char.custom.can_manage_inklings isApproved=this.char.is_approved isSelf=(eq this.char.id this.viewer.id) typeInfo=this.char.custom.inkling_types}}
  </div>
  ---END COPY---

  IMPORTANT DETAILS:

  ID MATCHING:
  - The id="inklings-tab-pane" below MUST match the href in profile-custom-tabs.snippet.hbs
  - Do NOT change this value

  PROPERTY NAMES:
  - The component uses: characterId, characterName, viewerId, isStaff, isApproved, isSelf, and typeInfo
  - These are passed from: this.char.id, this.char.name, this.viewer.id, this.char.custom.can_manage_inklings,
    this.char.is_approved, (eq this.char.id this.viewer.id), and this.char.custom.inkling_types
  - If your profile-custom.hbs uses different property names, update them here
  - Common alternatives: character instead of char, user instead of viewer, etc.
  - Check the rest of your profile-custom.hbs to see what names are used
  - characterName is used to display "Main Character" in the New Inkling
    form on the profile version (see WHY characterName IS NEEDED below) -
    if omitted, that field renders as an empty box.

  WHY characterName IS NEEDED:
  - In profile mode, the "New Inkling" form shows the profile being viewed as
    a static "Main Character" label (not a dropdown - see the "Yes, please
    ensure it is the profile owner and not the current user" note in
    inkling-create-form.js). It reads this from the characterName argument,
    not from any lookup of its own, so omitting it here leaves that field
    blank even though everything else on the form still works.

  WHY isStaff READS FROM char.custom.can_manage_inklings, NOT viewer.isStaff:
  - There is no standard "isStaff" field on the Ares web portal's viewer
    object. An earlier version of this snippet assumed one existed
    (viewer.isStaff) and the "+ New Inkling" button silently never showed
    for staff as a result - it was reading an undefined property.
  - can_manage_inklings is computed server-side via the plugin's own
    Inklings.can_manage_inklings? permission check (the same check the
    create-inkling API enforces), exposed through get_fields_for_viewing
    exactly like inkling_types below. This guarantees the client-side value
    always matches the server's real permission decision.

  TYPE PICKER DATA (typeInfo) AND STAFF OVERRIDE (isStaff):
  - Both char.custom.inkling_types and char.custom.can_manage_inklings are
    populated by custom_char_fields.snippet.rb's get_fields_for_viewing hook,
    NOT fetched by the component itself - this must be installed too, or the
    "New Inkling" type dropdown will be empty AND staff won't get their
    approval override.
  - See custom-install/custom_char_fields.snippet.rb, Step 2.

  ABOUT THE COMPONENT:
  {{inklings-tab}} renders the list and the "New Inkling" form. Clicking a
  row opens inkling-detail-modal (a second component it invokes internally,
  installed alongside it by plugin/install) - that's where messages, rolls,
  sharing, submission, and all staff actions live, in an ember-bootstrap
  modal. You only ever need to reference {{inklings-tab}} here; it wires up
  the detail modal itself.
  Its only dependency on the rest of the profile page is typeInfo (see above) -
  everything else it loads or sends itself via the gameApi service.

  IMPORTANT: Before using this snippet, you must complete Step 2 of the README
  (Install Web Portal Components), which includes copying inklings-tab.js and
  inkling-detail-modal.js to your webportal, AND install
  custom_char_fields.snippet.rb (Step 2 there) so char.custom.inkling_types is
  populated. The web portal integration is entirely optional - if you're
  running a MUSH-only game, you do not need this snippet or the components at
  all.
}}
